definitions.definition: A point ; the sharp end or top of anything that terminates in a point; as, the peak, or front, of a cap .
The highest value reached by some quantity in a time period .
examples: The stock market reached a peak in September 1929.

definitions.definition: ( geography ) The top , or one of the tops, of a hill , mountain , or range , ending in a point .
examples: They reached the peak after 8 hours of climbing.

definitions.definition: ( geography ) The whole hill or mountain, especially when isolated.
( clothing , UK ) visor ( horizontal part of a cap sticking out in front and shading the wearer's eyes )
( nautical ) The upper aftermost corner of a fore-and-aft sail.
( nautical ) The narrow part of a vessel 's bow , or the hold within it.
( nautical ) The extremity of an anchor fluke ; the bill .
( mathematics ) A local maximum of a function, e.g. for sine waves, each point at which the value of y is at its maximum.
